Foreign oil lubricants gaining China market share . Foreign - brand oil lubricants are grabbing a growing share of the Chinese market and are expected to account for 40 percent of sales within two years , the Xinhua news agency said . Foreign producers ' share of the 2 . 8 million - tonne annual market had soared to 16 percent by the end of 1995 from just 5 . 6 percent in 1991 , the agency said late on Tuesday . Sales of foreign oil lubricants had grown in response to the increase in the number of cars on China ' s roads , it quoted an industry newspaper as saying . Firms from the United States , Britain , Germany and Japan had set up 25 joint ventures in China , producing 450 , 000 tonnes of lubricants per year , it said . 
